<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Luxury resources are consumed by colonies. Having access to many luxury
resources raises a colony&#8217;s development level, producing more income.=
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;ms=
o-no-proof:
yes'>Each luxury resource at a colony raises the development level by
approximately 10%, thus when a colony has consistent access to 10 luxury
resources its development level will slowly rise to 100%.<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>

